text:
@Eric C. I think CC's soundtrack was lighthearted where it demanded (such as Another Termina, a bustling port town), and somber when it demanded (such as the Dead Sea or the battle with Miguel theme, Prisoners of Fate). I can't think of a single tune that didn't fit its location perfectly. The music really embodied the "sailing around tropical islands" theme of the game, which is why it's supposed to be lighthearted at times, but it can still tug at your heartstrings in the right places, like in the good ending.

The music in this game had such a unique feel and unique instruments, something no other game has really had.  This was the first game that really got me to notice video game music. FF7 had great music too, don't get me wrong, but there are so many more memorable songs in Chrono Cross! It's hard to think of a single tune in this game that wasn't spectacular. The music is just so vibrant and well composed.

And that's just some of the reasons why Chrono Cross has the greatest soundtrack of all time.
